This paper investigates human mating preferences using a large dataset from an online dating site, which suggests a focus on social interactions and behavior. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also uses statistical analysis and an evolutionary model, which could place it in cs.SD (Software Engineering) or cs.CY (Computational Geometry). Additionally, the study involves analyzing preferences in specific properties such as age, height, education, and income, which could fall under cs.CE (Computational Economics) or cs.SOC (Computational Social Science).
